        <p class="h1 h1headers">2018-2019 Salesian Message</p>
        <div class="contentfontsize">
            Our Salesian Message, also known as a Pastoral Theme, is a faith-based project, embraced by our entire school community. Each year, our message focuses on a new and different 
            theme, aimed at deepening our relationship to God, and one another. The annual theme can be seen in displays and lessons in each classroom. It can be heard each morning, during 
            announcements. Students of the Month are also chosen based on our school-wide theme. 
        </div>
        <img src="images/villa-family/listeninggod.webp" alt="Villa Madonna Listening for God" class="img-fluid rounded mx-auto d-block p-2" id="contentimages">
        <p class="lesserheader">We encourage your family to share our annual theme in your homes, in your own way. Here are some tips to help bring our theme alive in your home this year:</p>

        <!-- MASSIVE DUMP OF TEXT INCOMING -->
        <div class="contentfontsize">
            <strong>August & September -  Wonder :</strong> Embrace new beginnings, the new school year, a new job, even a new day or a new way of looking at things. Enjoy the wonder of the little things, 
            and share with each other something new you noticed in your day. Listen for God's message for YOU in new things around you.
        </div>
        <div class="contentfontsize pt-4">
            <strong>October & November – Gratitude:</strong> October is the month of the rosary and November brings Thanksgiving and the beginning of the holiday season. Our to-do lists grow long and our 
            patience may grow short. Call your attention several times a day to your many large and small blessings, commit to saying a daily Hail Mary as a family, or see who can name the 
            most blessings. Listen for God's many blessings.
        </div>
        <div class="contentfontsize pt-4">
            <strong>December & January– Integrity:</strong> Keep the focus on family and tradition during the Christmas season. Remind one another of the true meaning of Christmas, which is 
            love and the birth of Jesus. Embrace family traditions and church traditions. Bring out special decorations such as the Nativity scene or advent wreath, and share family recipes, 
            stories, and traditions. Make family new year resolutions. Slow down and don't let the season distract you from your most precious gift; your family. Listen for God in those 
            around you, and in traditions.
        </div>
        <div class="contentfontsize pt-4">
            <strong>February & March– Resilience:</strong> As the school year brings testing and many school events, stay strong and help one another manage stress in a healthy way. 
            Rely on healthy routines, discipline, and call on God for strength. Help each other overcome struggles, and not run from them. Be each other's source of strength. Listen for 
            God's message of strength. He never gives you more than you can bear. Sometimes your resilience is a sign of hope for those around you.
        </div>
        <div class="contentfontsize pt-4">
            <strong>April & May - Gentleness:</strong> As the school year comes to an end, so may our patience with one another. Ironically, doing something nice for another actually makes us 
            feel better even when we feel wronged. Look for a chance to help others as a family. Be present and make time for family discussions where they naturally happen (in the car, at bedtime, 
            at the kitchen counter). Listen for God's gentle message; imagine His gentle touch on your shoulder when you feel angry or depleted.
        </div>
